Transition
1. transform is css property lets you rotate, 
scale, skew, or translate an element

#file index.html

1. create a div section with id of box1 
and then set inner text to be Hi


#file style.css
2. take id of box1

transform: translateX()
transform: translateY()
transform: translate(x,y)

transform: rotateX()
transform: rotateY()
transform: rotateZ()

transform: scaleX(1);
        NOTE:
        1 means correspon to 100%
        1.1 means correspond to 110%
transform: scaleY()
transform: scale(x,y)

transform: skewX(deg);
transform: skewY(deg);
transform: skew(deg, deg);


3. we can apply more than one 
transformation at one time

transform: translateX(100px) rotateZ(45deg) scale(1.5);

4. these transformation can also be applied to a class 

#file index.html (only body)
<body>
    <div class="box" id="box1">Hi</div>
    <div class="box" id="box1">Hi</div>
    <div class="box" id="box1">Hi</div>
</body>

5. select class of box

#file style.css
.box{
     width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
    border: 4px solid;
    font-size: 5em;
    text-align: center;


    transform: translateX(100px) rotateZ(45deg) scale(.5)
}


#box1{
    background-color: hsl(160, 90%, 75%);
}


#box2{
    background-color: hsl(160, 90%, 55%);
}


#box3{
    background-color: hsl(160, 90%, 35%);
}







